President Obama expressed his sadness at the passing of Congressman John Murtha. He highlighted Murtha's dedication to his family and the people of Pennsylvania throughout his nearly 40-year career in Congress. Murtha's military service in the Marine Corps and his distinction as the first Vietnam War combat veteran elected to Congress shaped his passion for service. The President acknowledged Murtha's reputation as a strong and respected voice on national security issues. He extended his condolences to Murtha's wife of almost 55 years, Joyce, their three children, and the entire Murtha family.